    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3930315578" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3930315578" />
    <a title="Simon Pressinger" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/65026477-simon-pressinger"><img alt="Simon Pressinger" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613689021p2/65026477.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3930315578?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Simon Pressinger" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Simon Pressinger" href="/user/show/65026477-simon-pressinger">Simon Pressinger</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3930315578" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1057827071610266487">Lots of fun. I can only describe this as a soft science fiction adventure packed up in a wacky fantasy world. It’s full of endless crazy characters/species to enjoy. Think Gulliver’s Travels, but with less biting satire/social commentary and a lot more ketamine. Think Douglas Adams writing a series of Adult Swim episodes after having just woken up. It’s main weakness is the purely episodic nature of it, with no narrative arc to tie things together. Perhaps that’s also it’s strength. You can read</span>
  <span id="freeText1057827071610266487" style="display:none">Lots of fun. I can only describe this as a soft science fiction adventure packed up in a wacky fantasy world. It’s full of endless crazy characters/species to enjoy. Think Gulliver’s Travels, but with less biting satire/social commentary and a lot more ketamine. Think Douglas Adams writing a series of Adult Swim episodes after having just woken up. It’s main weakness is the purely episodic nature of it, with no narrative arc to tie things together. Perhaps that’s also it’s strength. You can read each chapter as dip-in episodes without having to commit to any serious story. It might be 700 pages, but with the illustrations, they go fast.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1057827071610266487" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

